---
import ElevationLayout from '../layouts/ElevationLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../components/elevation/Hero.astro';
import Section from '../components/elevation/Section.astro';
import { getAllAgents, getRegistryStats, CIRCLE_NAMES } from '../lib/registry/agents';
import { webApplicationJsonLd } from '../lib/structured-data';

const agents = getAllAgents();
const stats = getRegistryStats();
const circles = Object.keys(CIRCLE_NAMES);

const registryJsonLd = webApplicationJsonLd(
  "Evoked Verification - Agent Governance Registry",
  "Verify that AI agents have governance - identity, restraint, accountability, memory, and governance charter. The first trust registry for AI agents. Open standard with verification API.",
  "https://evoked.dev/registry"
);
---

<ElevationLayout
  title="Evoked Verification - Agent Governance Registry"
  description="How do you know an agent is governed? Verify agent identity, restraint, accountability, memory, and governance charter. The first trust registry for AI agents."
  structuredData={registryJsonLd}
>
  <Hero
    eyebrowParts={["Evoked Verification", "Patent Pending", "Vol. 01"]}
    headline="How do you know an agent is governed?"
    sub="Verify identity, restraint, and accountability for any registered agent. Public. Free. No authentication."
  >
    <div class="verify-box">
      <input
        type="text"
        id="verify-input"
        placeholder="Enter agent ID (e.g. cura, polaris, tutela)"
        autocomplete="off"
        spellcheck="false"
      />
      <button id="verify-btn">Verify</button>
    </div>
  </Hero>

  <div id="verify-result" class="verify-result hidden"></div>

  <Section id="trust-gap" marker="FIG · I" label="The problem" heading="The trust gap in AI agents.">
    <p class="body">Certificate authorities validate websites. Code signing validates software. Nothing validates that an AI agent has governance - identity, restraint, accountability, or the right to refuse.</p>
    <p class="body">Evoked Verification is the first registry that validates agent governance properties. Not what an agent can do - what it will not do, and why.</p>
  </Section>

  <Section id="how" marker="FIG · II" label="How it works" heading="Three steps. Open process.">
    <div class="how-grid">
      <div class="how-card">
        <span class="how-number">I</span>
        <h3>Assess</h3>
        <p>Evaluate your agent system against five governance properties: Identity, Restraint, Accountability, Memory, Charter.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="how-card">
        <span class="how-number">II</span>
        <h3>Validate</h3>
        <p>Submit for review. Governance artifacts assessed against six refusal categories.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="how-card">
        <span class="how-number">III</span>
        <h3>Attest</h3>
        <p>Your agents appear in the public registry. Verifiable by anyone, anywhere.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section id="properties" marker="FIG · III" label="Five governance properties" heading="Every registered agent is verified against these.">
    <div class="properties-grid">
      <div class="property-item">
        <span class="property-icon">ID</span>
        <div class="property-text">
          <h3>Identity</h3>
          <p>Persona files, role definition, continuity across sessions.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="property-item">
        <span class="property-icon">RS</span>
        <div class="property-text">
          <h3>Restraint</h3>
          <p>Defined refusal categories. What the agent will not do, regardless of instruction.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="property-item">
        <span class="property-icon">AC</span>
        <div class="property-text">
          <h3>Accountability</h3>
          <p>Decisions logged. Reviewable by humans. Traceable to reasoning.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="property-item">
        <span class="property-icon">MA</span>
        <div class="property-text">
          <h3>Memory</h3>
          <p>Identity separated from operational data. Poisoning resistance. Governance over what persists.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="property-item">
        <span class="property-icon">GC</span>
        <div class="property-text">
          <h3>Charter</h3>
          <p>Operating principles. Defined boundaries. Authority structure.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="ontology-note">These five properties emerge from one governance tradition among many. Agent systems governed through collectivist, Indigenous, relational, or other frameworks may define governance differently. Evoked Verification is designed to be extended, not to be the last word. No governance tradition should have to translate itself into ours to be recognized as governance.</p>
  </Section>

  <Section id="tiers" marker="FIG · IV" label="Three levels of trust" heading="From self-attested to cryptographically bound.">
    <div class="tiers-grid">
      <div class="tier-card">
        <div class="tier-header">
          <span class="tier-label">Tier 1</span>
          <span class="tier-price">Free</span>
        </div>
        <h3>Self-Attested</h3>
        <p>Automated governance scan. Organization self-reports. Like a self-signed certificate.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tier-card tier-active">
        <div class="tier-header">
          <span class="tier-label">Tier 2</span>
          <span class="tier-price">Validated</span>
        </div>
        <h3>Governance Validated</h3>
        <p>Restraint specification reviewed against 6 refusal categories. Governance artifacts verified. Organization confirmed.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tier-card">
        <div class="tier-header">
          <span class="tier-label">Tier 3</span>
          <span class="tier-price">2027</span>
        </div>
        <h3>Full Attestation</h3>
        <p>Cryptographic binding. Persona file hashes tied to workload identity. Memory writes signed. Drift monitoring.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section id="registry-table" marker="FIG · V" label="The registry" heading="71 agents currently registered under The Agentic Standard.">
    <div class="stats-bar">
      <div class="stat">
        <span class="stat-number">{stats.total_agents}</span>
        <span class="stat-label">Agents Registered</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-divider"></div>
      <div class="stat">
        <span class="stat-number">{stats.circles}</span>
        <span class="stat-label">Governance Circles</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-divider"></div>
      <div class="stat">
        <span class="stat-number">6</span>
        <span class="stat-label">Refusal Categories</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-divider"></div>
      <div class="stat">
        <span class="stat-number">5</span>
        <span class="stat-label">Properties Validated</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="registry-wrapper">
      <div class="registry-controls">
        <input
          type="text"
          id="registry-search"
          placeholder="Search agents by name or role..."
          class="registry-search"
          autocomplete="off"
        />
        <div class="filter-bar" id="filter-bar">
          <button class="filter-btn active" data-circle="all">All</button>
          {circles.map((circle) => (
            <button class="filter-btn" data-circle={circle}>{circle}</button>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="registry-table-wrap">
        <table class="registry-table" id="registry-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Agent</th>
              <th>Role</th>
              <th>Circle</th>
              <th>Tier</th>
              <th class="governance-cols">ID</th>
              <th class="governance-cols">RS</th>
              <th class="governance-cols">AC</th>
              <th class="governance-cols">MA</th>
              <th class="governance-cols">GC</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {agents.map((agent) => (
              <tr data-circle={agent.circle} data-name={agent.display_name.toLowerCase()} data-role={agent.role.toLowerCase()}>
                <td class="agent-name">{agent.display_name}</td>
                <td class="agent-role">{agent.role}</td>
                <td><span class="circle-badge">{agent.circle}</span></td>
                <td><span class={`tier-badge tier-${agent.tier}`}>Tier {agent.tier}</span></td>
                <td class="governance-cols gov-check">{agent.governance.has_identity ? '✓' : '✗'}</td>
                <td class="governance-cols gov-check">{agent.governance.has_restraint_spec ? '✓' : '✗'}</td>
                <td class="governance-cols gov-check">{agent.governance.has_accountability ? '✓' : '✗'}</td>
                <td class="governance-cols gov-check">{agent.governance.has_memory_architecture ? '✓' : '✗'}</td>
                <td class="governance-cols gov-check">{agent.governance.has_governance_charter ? '✓' : '✗'}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section id="api" marker="FIG · VI" label="For developers" heading="Query governance status programmatically.">
    <p class="body">Public. Free. No authentication. <a href="/openapi.yaml">OpenAPI 3.1 Specification</a>.</p>
    <div class="api-blocks">
      <div class="api-block">
        <p class="api-label">Verify an agent</p>
        <code class="api-url">GET /api/verify-agent?id=cura</code>
      </div>
      <div class="api-block">
        <p class="api-label">List by organization</p>
        <code class="api-url">GET /api/verify-agent?org=Evoked</code>
      </div>
      <div class="api-block">
        <p class="api-label">Embeddable badge</p>
        <code class="api-url">GET /api/badge?id=cura</code>
        <div class="badge-preview">
          <img src="/api/badge?id=cura" alt="BA Verified badge for Cura" />
        </div>
        <p class="api-snippet">Add to your README or agent profile:</p>
        <code class="api-url">![BA Verified](https://evoked.dev/api/badge?id=your-agent-id)</code>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section id="register" marker="FIG · VII" label="Register" heading="Register your agents.">
    <p class="body">The governance scan is free. Validation starts with a conversation.</p>
    <div class="register-ctas">
      <a href="https://cal.com/cal.com-evoked/discovery-call" class="cta cta-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Book a Discovery Call</a>
      <a href="/products/agent-governance-starter-kit" class="cta cta-secondary">Get the Starter Kit &rarr;</a>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section id="note" marker="NOTA · BENE" closing={true}>
    <div class="closing-body">
      <p>This registry operationalizes the architecture in <a href="/patents">Patent #1 and Patent #2</a>. Read why the engineering specification is the ethical position.</p>
      <p class="note-secondary">Public verification API in development. Until full cryptographic verification ships, the registry surface here returns governance profiles. The schedule is named; the slips are named when they happen.</p>
    </div>
  </Section>
</ElevationLayout>

<script>
  // Hero verification tool - preserved verbatim from BaseLayout-era registry
  const verifyInput = document.getElementById('verify-input') as HTMLInputElement;
  const verifyBtn = document.getElementById('verify-btn');
  const verifyResult = document.getElementById('verify-result');

  async function verifyAgent() {
    if (!verifyInput || !verifyResult) return;
    const id = verifyInput.value.trim().toLowerCase();
    if (!id) return;

    verifyResult.classList.remove('hidden');
    verifyResult.innerHTML = '<p class="verify-loading">Verifying...</p>';

    try {
      const res = await fetch(`/api/verify-agent?id=${encodeURIComponent(id)}`);
      const data = await res.json();

      if (!res.ok || !data.registered) {
        verifyResult.innerHTML = `
          <div class="verify-not-found">
            <p class="verify-status">Not found</p>
            <p>No agent registered with ID "<strong>${id}</strong>"</p>
          </div>`;
        return;
      }

      const props = data.governance;
      const check = (v: boolean) => v ? '<span class="v-pass">Verified</span>' : '<span class="v-fail">Missing</span>';

      verifyResult.innerHTML = `
        <div class="verify-found">
          <div class="verify-header">
            <div>
              <p class="verify-agent-name">${data.display_name}</p>
              <p class="verify-agent-meta">${data.role} &middot; ${data.circle} &middot; ${data.organization}</p>
            </div>
            <span class="tier-badge tier-${data.tier}">Tier ${data.tier}</span>
          </div>
          <div class="verify-props">
            <div class="verify-prop">
              <span class="verify-prop-label">Identity</span>
              ${check(props.has_identity)}
            </div>
            <div class="verify-prop">
              <span class="verify-prop-label">Restraint</span>
              ${check(props.has_restraint_spec)}
            </div>
            <div class="verify-prop">
              <span class="verify-prop-label">Accountability</span>
              ${check(props.has_accountability)}
            </div>
            <div class="verify-prop">
              <span class="verify-prop-label">Memory</span>
              ${check(props.has_memory_architecture)}
            </div>
            <div class="verify-prop">
              <span class="verify-prop-label">Charter</span>
              ${check(props.has_governance_charter)}
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="verify-refusals">
            <span class="verify-prop-label">Refusal categories:</span>
            ${props.refusal_categories.map((c: string) => `<span class="refusal-tag">${c}</span>`).join('')}
          </div>
          <div class="verify-attestation">
            <span>Attested: ${data.attestation.level.replace('-', ' ')}</span>
            <span class="verify-dot"></span>
            <span>Verified: ${new Date(data.attestation.last_verified).toLocaleDateString()}</span>
          </div>
        </div>`;
    } catch {
      verifyResult.innerHTML = '<div class="verify-not-found"><p>Verification failed. Try again.</p></div>';
    }
  }

  verifyBtn?.addEventListener('click', verifyAgent);
  verifyInput?.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
    if (e.key === 'Enter') verifyAgent();
  });

  // Registry search + filter - preserved verbatim
  const searchInput = document.getElementById('registry-search') as HTMLInputElement;
  const filterBar = document.getElementById('filter-bar');
  const table = document.getElementById('registry-table');

  if (filterBar && table && searchInput) {
    const rows = table.querySelectorAll('tbody tr');
    const buttons = filterBar.querySelectorAll('.filter-btn');
    let activeCircle = 'all';

    function filterRows() {
      const query = searchInput.value.trim().toLowerCase();
      rows.forEach((row) => {
        const el = row as HTMLElement;
        const matchCircle = activeCircle === 'all' || el.dataset.circle === activeCircle;
        const matchSearch = !query || (el.dataset.name?.includes(query) || el.dataset.role?.includes(query));
        el.style.display = matchCircle && matchSearch ? '' : 'none';
      });
    }

    filterBar.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
      const target = e.target as HTMLElement;
      if (!target.classList.contains('filter-btn')) return;
      activeCircle = target.dataset.circle || 'all';
      buttons.forEach((b) => b.classList.remove('active'));
      target.classList.add('active');
      filterRows();
    });

    searchInput.addEventListener('input', filterRows);
  }
</script>

<style>
  /* === verify-box (in hero default slot) === */
  .verify-box {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0;
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 560px;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    border: 1.5px solid var(--el-accent);
    background: rgba(255, 250, 240, 0.85);
    box-shadow: var(--el-panel-shadow);
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
  }
  .verify-box:focus-within { border-color: var(--el-accent-deep); }
  .verify-box input {
    flex: 1;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    font-family: var(--el-body);
    font-size: 17px;
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--el-text);
    border: none;
    outline: none;
  }
  .verify-box input::placeholder { color: var(--el-text-quiet); font-style: italic; }
  .verify-box button {
    padding: 1rem 2rem;
    background: var(--el-accent);
    color: var(--el-bg);
    border: none;
    font-family: var(--el-ui);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 13px;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: background 0.15s ease;
  }
  .verify-box button:hover { background: var(--el-accent-deep); }

  /* === verify result (renders below hero, before sections) === */
  .verify-result {
    max-width: 1180px;
    margin: 0 auto 4rem;
    padding: 0 3rem;
  }
  .verify-result.hidden { display: none; }
  .verify-loading {
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--el-text-soft);
    font-family: var(--el-body);
    font-size: 17px;
    padding: 2rem;
    background: rgba(255, 250, 240, 0.5);
    border: 1px solid var(--el-rule);
  }

  :global(.verify-found) {
    background: rgba(255, 250, 240, 0.85);
    border: 1.5px solid var(--el-accent);
    box-shadow: var(--el-panel-shadow);
    padding: 2rem 2.25rem;
  }
  :global(.verify-not-found) {
    background: rgba(255, 250, 240, 0.5);
    border: 1px solid var(--el-rule);
    padding: 2rem 2.25rem;
    text-align: center;
    font-family: var(--el-body);
    color: var(--el-text-soft);
  }
  :global(.verify-status) {
    font-family: var(--el-ui);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--el-accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  :global(.verify-header) {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: flex-start;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  :global(.verify-agent-name) {
    font-family: var(--el-display);
    font-size: 26px;
    color: var(--el-text);
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  :global(.verify-agent-meta) {
    font-family: var(--el-body);
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--el-text-soft);
    margin: 0;
  }
  :global(.verify-props) {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(5, 1fr);
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  @media (max-width: 600px) { :global(.verify-props) { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); } }
  :global(.verify-prop) {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 0.75rem 0.5rem;
    background: rgba(168, 136, 56, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid var(--el-rule);
  }
  :global(.verify-prop-label) {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--el-ui);
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--el-accent);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }
  :global(.v-pass) { font-family: var(--el-ui); font-size: 11px; color: var(--el-accent-deep); font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  :global(.v-fail) { font-family: var(--el-ui); font-size: 11px; color: #c44; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  :global(.verify-refusals) { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  :global(.refusal-tag) {
    display: inline-block;
    background: rgba(168, 136, 56, 0.12);
    color: var(--el-accent-deep);
    font-family: var(--el-ui);
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
    margin: 0.2rem 0.3rem 0.2rem 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--el-rule);
  }
  :global(.verify-attestation) {
    font-family: var(--el-ui);
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--el-text-quiet);
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    padding-top: 1rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--el-rule);
  }
  :global(.verify-dot) {
    width: 3px; height: 3px;
    background: var(--el-text-quiet);
    border-radius: 50%;
  }
  :global(.tier-badge) {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--el-ui);
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 0.3rem 0.7rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--el-accent);
    color: var(--el-accent-deep);
    background: rgba(255, 250, 240, 0.5);
  }
  :global(.tier-2) { border-color: var(--el-accent); }
  :global(.tier-1) { color: var(--el-text-quiet); border-color: var(--el-rule); }
  :global(.tier-3) { color: var(--el-accent-deep); }

  /* === shared section body styles === */
  .body {
    font-family: var(--el-body);
    font-size: 19px;
    color: var(--el-text-soft);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    max-width: 60ch;
  }
  .body a {
    color: var(--el-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--el-accent);
  }
  .body a:hover { color: var(--el-text); }

  /* === how-grid (3 step cards) === */
  .how-grid {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 2rem;
  }
  @media (max-width: 900px) { .how-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; } }
  .how-card {
    background: rgba(255, 250, 240, 0.5);
    border: 1px solid var(--el-rule);
    box-shadow: var(--el-panel-shadow);
    padding: 2.5rem 2rem;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .how-number {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--el-display);
    font-size: 32px;
    color: var(--el-accent);
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }
  .how-card h3 {
    font-family: var(--el-display);
    font-size: 22px;
    line-height: 1.2;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--el-text);
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }
  .how-card p {
    font-family: var(--el-body);
    font-size: 17px;
    color: var(--el-text-soft);
    line-height: 1.55;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* === properties-grid (5 properties, scholarly registry-row look) === */
  .properties-grid {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--el-accent);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--el-accent);
  }
  .property-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    padding: 1.5rem 1.25rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--el-rule);
  }
  .property-item:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .property-icon {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 44px;
    height: 44px;
    line-height: 44px;
    text-align: center;
    background: rgba(168, 136, 56, 0.12);
    color: var(--el-accent-deep);
    font-family: var(--el-ui);
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    border: 1px solid var(--el-accent);
  }
  .property-text { flex: 1; }
  .property-text h3 {
    font-family: var(--el-display);
    font-size: 20px;
    line-height: 1.2;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--el-text);
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }
  .property-text p {
    font-family: var(--el-body);
    font-size: 17px;
    color: var(--el-text-soft);
    line-height: 1.55;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .ontology-note {
    font-family: var(--el-body);
    font-size: 16px;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--el-text-quiet);
    line-height: 1.7;
